  "prompt": "What is the sum of all the integers less than 100 which leave a remainder 2 when divided by 5?",
  "response": "Let's solve this step by step:\n\n1) First, let's understand what numbers leave a remainder of 2 when divided by 5\n   \u2022 These would be numbers in the form 5k + 2\n   \u2022 Some examples: 2, 7, 12, 17, 22, 27, 32, 37, 42, 47, 52, 57, 62, 67, 72, 77, 82, 87, 92, 97\n\n2) Let's find the first and last numbers in this sequence less than 100\n   \u2022 First number: 2\n   \u2022 Last number: 97\n\n3) Now, let's count how many such numbers are there\n   \u2022 These numbers follow the pattern: 2, 7, 12, 17, ..., 97\n   \u2022 We can calculate how many are in the sequence\n   \u2022 Last number is 97, first number is 2\n   \u2022 Difference between consecutive terms is 5\n   \u2022 We can use arithmetic sequence formula to count\n\n4) Number of terms in the sequence\n   \u2022 First term a = 2\n   \u2022 Last term l = 97\n   \u2022 Common difference d = 5\n   \u2022 Number of terms n = (l - a)/d + 1\n   \u2022 n = (97 - 2)/5 + 1\n   \u2022 n = 95/5 + 1\n   \u2022 n = 19 + 1\n   \u2022 n = 20\n\n5) Sum of arithmetic sequence\n   \u2022 Sum = n(a + l)/2\n   \u2022 Sum = 20(2 + 97)/2\n   \u2022 Sum = 20 * 99/2\n   \u2022 Sum = 20 * 49.5\n   \u2022 Sum = 990\n\nThe answer is 990.\n\nLet's verify:\n2 + 7 + 12 + 17 + 22 + 27 + 32 + 37 + 42 + 47 + 52 + 57 + 62 + 67 + 72 + 77 + 82 + 87 + 92 + 97 = 990 \u2713\n\nThe sum is 990.",
